items.name: The Babylon Project
items.title: The Babylon Project
items.headline: Welcome to the Babylon 5 Wiki!
items.desc:
This wiki is dedicated to the show Babylon 5, which is an American space opera television series created by writer and producer J. Michael Straczynski, under the Babylonian Productions label.

Set between the years 2258 and 2262, it depicts a future where Earth has sovereign states, and a unifying Earthgov. Colonies within the solar system, and beyond, make up the Earth Alliance, and contact has been made with other spacefaring races.

Join our wiki!

items.name: Doom Wiki
items.title: Doom Wiki
items.headline: Doom Wiki
items.desc: Doom Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia about id Software's classic games Doom and Doom II, as well as games based on the Doom engine. Doom is an iconic game that consolidated the first-person shooter genre. With a science fiction and horror style, it gives the players the role of marines who find themselves in the focal point of an invasion from hell. The game introduced deathmatch and cooperative play in the explicit sense, and helped further the practice of allowing and encouraging fan-made modifications of commercial video games.

items.name: The Sims Wiki
items.title: The Sims Wiki
items.headline: The Sims Wiki - the ultimate encyclopedia on The Sims
items.desc:
The Sims Wiki was founded in 2005 and is an encyclopedia devoted to The Sims series developed by Maxis and EA Games. With over 7,000 articles as of January 2013, it has a wide array of information for whatever aspect of the series you are looking for. We even have a dedicated namespace for fanon content where you can write about your own character's adventures.

Our community is very welcoming to new users and we have various different social aspects, such as an off-topic forum, Chat, an IRC channel, social media pages, a Steam group amongst other things to engage the community. So why not drop in, check the place out and get involved? Enjoy!

items.name: SGCommand
items.title: SGCommand
items.headline: Stargate Wiki
items.desc: Stargate Wiki is a comprehensive database dedicated to Stargate:SG-1, Stargate:Atlantis, Stargate:Universe, Stargate:Infinity, Stargate Origins, and the Stargate movies, books, and other media. Information covers characters, cast, planets, races, and more.

items.name: The Firefly and Serenity Database
items.title: The Firefly and Serenity Database
items.headline: Welcome to The Firefly and Serenity Database!
items.desc:
Welcome to the encyclopedia based on Joss Whedon's series and film that anyone can edit.

Firefly is a science fiction television series that premiered in the United States and Canada on September 20, 2002. Its naturalistic future setting, modeled after traditional Western movie motifs, presents an atypical science fiction backdrop for the narrative. It was conceived by writer and director Joss Whedon, creator of Buffy the Vampire Slayer and Angel, under his production tag, Mutant Enemy.

Serenity is a 2005 science-fiction film written and directed by Joss Whedon. It is set in the universe of the canceled Fox science fiction television series Firefly, taking place a few months after the events of the final episode.

items.name: Final Fantasy Wiki
items.title: Final Fantasy Wiki
items.headline: Final Fantasy Wiki
items.desc: Covering one of the most well-known video game series of all-time, Final Fantasy Wiki is dedicated to collecting information from elements of storyline and characters to gameplay and Entertainment, as well as everything in between.

items.name: Pro Wrestling
items.title: Pro Wrestling
items.headline: Welcome to the Professional Wrestling Wiki!
items.desc: The Pro Wrestling Wiki is a collaborative project to create a dynamic resource for information on professional wrestling. It is a place to find general information about all your favorite professional wrestling promotions and personalities, past and present. Read about the latest in matches, T.V. episodes, tag teams, merchandise and more!

items.name: RuneScape Wiki
items.title: RuneScape Wiki
items.headline: The RuneScape Wiki
items.desc:
Started in April of 2005, the RuneScape Wiki's goal is to remain a vast, knowledgeable source for all things in RuneScape.

The RuneScape Wiki aims to be a competitor to all major RuneScape fansites. Guides to new quests or holiday events, for example, can be made in under an hour, far ahead of other fansites.

It contains a guide to every quest and treasure trail, and over 26,000 articles about items, locations and monsters.


RuneScape is copyright 1999 - 2014 Jagex Ltd. The RuneScape Wiki is in no way affiliated with Jagex.

items.name: InuYasha
items.title: InuYasha
items.headline: Welcome to the InuYasha Wiki
items.desc: Inuyasha Wiki is dedicated to the long-running popular manga and anime series, InuYasha. InuYasha is a supernatural action-adventure romantic-comedy, set in the feudal era of Japan. The wiki has over 1000 pages of information on the InuYasha series, covering hundreds of characters, episode and manga chapter summaries, and many other topics related to the franchise.

items.name: Law and Order
items.title: Law and Order
items.headline: Law and Order Wiki
items.desc: Law and Order Wiki is a collaborative database for the Law and Order universe. The wiki contains information about the original Law and Order series as well as its spin-offs: Law and Order: SVU, Criminal Intent, Trial by Jury, UK, Los Angeles, and other related media releases.

items.name: EverQuest 2 Wiki
items.title: EverQuest 2 Wiki
items.headline: EQ2i
items.desc: EQ2i is an award-winning wiki about the MMORPG EverQuest 2 by Sony Online Entertainment, featuring nearly 60,000 pages on a wide variety of topics, such as quests, equipment, items, monsters, NPCs, and zones.

items.name: Hitchhikers
items.title: Hitchhikers
items.headline: Welcome to the Hitchhiker wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to Hitchhikers Wiki!  A wiki dedicated to the truly amazing works of Douglas Adams and Eoin Colfer that anyone can edit. 

First published as a comedic radio series in 1978 Douglas Adams series became an international multi-media phenomenon. His trilogy in six-parts has received acclaim through the years, the last being written by Eoin Colfer. 

Many other adaptations from the original radio series has seen as Radio and TV Series as well as comic book adaptations. And in later years saw the development of a Film and Computer Game.

items.name: Nickelodeon
items.title: Nickelodeon
items.headline: Nickipedia, the Nickelodeon Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to Nickipedia, the Nickelodeon Wiki that anyone can edit, including you! Nickipedia is a fan-made Nickelodeon information database collaboration. We are not affiliated with Nickelodeon, but we are a comprehensive resource for everything to do with Nickelodeon. If you're a fan and want to share your knowledge and passion, join us today!

items.name: TibiaWiki
items.title: TibiaWiki
items.headline: TibiaWiki - the english wiki about Tibia
items.desc: With over 15,000 pages, at TibiaWiki you will find information for practically everything that exists in Tibia. Whether you are looking for text of a book, want to know how to obtain a certain item, or need hints for a quest, we've got you covered. Some nice tools like the Outfiter, a minimap tool of whole Tibia and Loot Statistics make us worth your visit as well.

items.name: TibiaWikiPT
items.title: TibiaWikiPT
items.headline: TibiaWiki - a wiki brasileira sobre Tibia
items.desc: Com mais de 600 páginas, você vai encontrar praticamente tudo que sobre Tibia aqui na Tibia wiki. Se você estiver procurando texto de um livro, quiser saber como obter um certo item, ou precisar de dicas para uma missão, nós podemos te ajudar! Nós também temos estatísticas de Loot. Venha conferir e se divertir você também!

items.name: Horror Film Wiki
items.title: Horror Film Wiki
items.headline: Learn more about the Horror Wiki...
items.desc: The Horror Film Wiki is a database for all things horror film related. We have articles on films, characters, and even the cast and crew! We are always looking for new and experienced editors to add to our rankings. Feel free to drop by and say hi! We look forward to adding you to our community, welcome to your new horror-loving family!

items.name: White Wolf
items.title: White Wolf
items.headline: White Wolf Wiki
items.desc: The White Wolf Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia project where you can find out about the worlds and systems created by White Wolf, the producer of many roleplaying games, board games, card games, novels and more. The wiki regularly updates their content with latest and upcoming releases for all White Wolf games.

items.name: DC Animated Universe
items.title: DC Animated Universe
items.headline: DC Animated Universe Wiki
items.desc: DC Animated Wiki is devoted to the DC Animated Universe. It provides extensive coverage of everything pertaining to the line of DC-based shows, which started with Batman: The Animated Series in 1992 and concluded with Justice League Unlimited in 2006.

items.name: MMKB
items.title: MMKB
items.headline: Mega Man Knowledge Database
items.desc: Mega Man Knowledge Database is a community site for the Mega Man video game series. The wiki contains all information related to the franchise, such as the games, characters, enemies, items, cartoons, anime, comics, manga, and more.

items.name: Teletraan I: The Transformers Wiki
items.title: Teletraan I: The Transformers Wiki
items.headline: Transformers Wiki
items.desc: Transformers Wiki is a knowledge base devoted to the Transformers franchise, covering the TV series, comic books, Entertainment, real-life people, objects, technology, planets, and anything else related to Transformers.

items.name: MicroNations Fandom
items.title: MicroNations Fandom
items.headline: Now Entering MicroWiki
items.desc: Ever wanted to create a country? Well, this is a good place to start.

items.name: StarCraft Wiki
items.title: StarCraft Wiki
items.headline: StarCraft Wiki
items.desc: StarCraft Wiki is a community database dedicated to documenting the StarCraft universe. Within its 4,500 pages you'll find detailed information on the games, expansions, units, characters, races, storyline, and more.

items.name: Full House
items.title: Full House
items.headline: Welcome to the Full House Wiki
items.desc: A collaborative website about the 1987-95 American sitcom Full House

items.name: Futurama Wiki
items.title: Futurama Wiki
items.headline: Come visit the Futurama Wiki today!
items.desc: Futurama is a community-run encyclopedia for the popular animated series, Futurama. Futurama is an American sitcom series creаted by Matt Groening and developed by Groening and David X. Cohen, is an animated television show that focuses on the lives of delivery boy Fry, Leela, and Bender in the futuristic 31st century.

items.name: Sailor Moon Wiki
items.title: Sailor Moon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Sailor Moon Wiki!
items.desc:
The Sailor Moon Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia for everything related to the metaseries Sailor Moon. 

"Bishōjo Senshi Sailor Moon" refers to the original incarnation of Sailor Moon, which was a manga created and illustrated by Naoko Takeuchi and later adapted to a popular anime series that spanned 200 episodes, three feature films, five specials, and five memorials. Other adaptions of the Sailor Moon series include a live-action TV series, a series of musicals, and a second anime adaption that premiered in July 2014. 

New editors are welcome! We are really grateful for any help on pages, templates, and other things that can improve this wiki!

items.name: Moviepedia
items.title: Moviepedia
items.headline: Welcome to Moviepedia
items.desc: Welcome to Moviepedia, an encyclopedic site of information on past, present, and future movies! Updated by fans, Moviepedia is a work in process, but it is sure to hold the latest information about upcoming releases that you might be interested in! Enter now to learn more about what you can do to help!

items.name: Xenosaga Wiki
items.title: Xenosaga Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Xenosaga Wiki
items.desc: Were are a wiki dedicated to the science-fiction, Role-Playing-Game series, Xenosaga, developed by Monolith Soft and published by Namco. The series currently consists of three main games with three spin-offs, as well as an animated series. Come join us and read all about it!

items.name: Animal Crossing Wiki
items.title: Animal Crossing Wiki
items.headline: Animal Crossing Wiki
items.desc: The Animal Crossing Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia for everything related to the Animal Crossing series. There are 1,677 articles and growing since this wiki was founded in August 2005. The wiki format allows anyone to create or edit any article, so we can all work together to create a comprehensive database for the Animal Crossing series.

items.name: James Bond Wiki
items.title: James Bond Wiki
items.headline: A true information goldmine about the world's greatest spy, James Bond.
items.desc: Bond... James Bond. The world's great spy since 1953. First penned by Ian Fleming in the novel "Casino Royale", the legendary 007 has appeared in 39 official novels (14 by Fleming) and 24 films over the past 60+ years. The James Bond Wikia has chronicled the novel, video game, and cinematic adventures from 1953's "Casino Royale" to the newest instalment, 2015's "Spectre".

items.name: Metal Gear Wiki
items.title: Metal Gear Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Metal Gear Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Metal Gear Wiki, your resource for all things Metal Gear! The Metal Gear Wiki is the ultimate resource of knowledge for the Metal Gear video game franchise. In addition to all canonical and non-canonical games, the wiki also covers remakes, updates, Entertainment, and even the people who develop the games.

items.name: Wikitroid
items.title: Wikitroid
items.headline: Wikitroid
items.desc: Metroid Wiki "Wikitroid" is a  community-run database that aims to create the best resource for Metroid, a series of video games produced by Nintendo. The Metroid games chronicle the missions of bounty hunter Samus Aran in a science fiction setting which contains many similarities to the Alien film franchise. The wiki has nearly 3500 pages of content devoted to the game series.

items.name: Star Wars Fanon
items.title: Star Wars Fanon
items.headline: Star Wars Fanon Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to Star Wars Fanon, a community of fan authors writing stories set in the galaxy far, far away. Dive in today and post all of your fan-created stories, characters, novels, and more!

items.name: Inheriwiki
items.title: Inheriwiki
items.headline: Inheriwiki, the Inheritance Cycle Wiki
items.desc: The Inheritance Wiki (Inheriwiki) is dedicated to The Inheritance Cycle (previously known as the Inheritance Trilogy), a series of high-fantasy novels by homeschooled author Christopher Paolini. The series follows the exploits of Eragon, a teenage orphan who becomes the first of a new order of Dragon Riders. It covers the detailed Universe of the Cycle, written in in-universe style, and also real-world actors, authors and topics connected to the Cycle.

items.name: Age of Empires Series Wiki
items.title: Age of Empires Series Wiki
items.headline: Age of Empires Wiki
items.desc: Age of Empires Wiki is about the "Age of Empires Series", the history-based, original real time strategy games of Ensemble Studios published by Microsoft Game Studios. The wiki has information about all of the Age of Empire series as well as its spin-offs, Age of Mythology.

items.name: The Dark Shadows Wiki
items.title: The Dark Shadows Wiki
items.headline: The Dark Shadows Wiki
items.desc: The Dark Shadows Wiki is a collaborative project designed to document everything related to the various incarnations of the Dark Shadows franchise. The Wiki format allows anyone to create or edit any article (that includes you!), helping provide a complete, up-to-date database for fans. Join us and share your love and knowledge for Dark Shadows!

items.name: MUGEN Database
items.title: MUGEN Database
items.headline: Welcome to the MUGEN Database!
items.desc:
The MUGEN Database is a wiki-based database that lists characters, stages and various other aspects of the customisable fighting game engine, M.U.G.E.N. For those that don't know, M.U.G.E.N (also known simply as MUGEN) is a freeware 2D fighting game engine designed by Elecbyte.

Originally released as DOS M.U.G.E.N in 1999, M.U.G.E.N has since evolved significantly, with the most recent version being 1.1, which adds 32-bit colour support, stage zooming and more. M.U.G.E.N also has a large community consisting of both players and creators - yes, being a fighting game engine, it is possible to create your very own characters, stages and even your own fighting game!

items.name: The Calvin and Hobbes Wiki
items.title: The Calvin and Hobbes Wiki
items.headline: Like Calvin and Hobbes? Join the wiki then!
items.desc: Do you like an old comic strip about a boy and his tiger named Hobbes? If so, I suggest you learn more about Calvin and Hobbes. And what better way to do it then join the wiki? We are always looking for new users, and it would be absolutely awesome if you joined! We have information on Susie, Rosalyn, GROSS, Hobbes, and every character. Join the Calvin and Hobbes Wiki!

items.name: Wiki 24
items.title: Wiki 24
items.headline: Wiki 24
items.desc: Wiki 24 is a database for the long-running, popular series 24. The show, starring Kiefer Sutherland as Jack Bauer, focuses on the efforts of the fictional Counter Terrorist Unit in Los Angeles, in its eighth season in New York, and in its seventh season, the FBI in Washington, D.C.. Each episode takes place over the course of one hour, depicting events "as they occur" in real time; a full season of twenty-four episodes thus covers a full day.

items.name: Indiana Jones Wiki
items.title: Indiana Jones Wiki
items.headline: The Indiana Jones resource built by fans like you!
items.desc: The Indiana Jones Wiki is an online encyclopedia that anyone can edit, based on the Indiana Jones saga created by George Lucas. Launched in September 2005, this site strives to be a comprehensive reference for Indiana Jones fiction, including the feature films, television series, novels, comics and video games. As you read about Indiana's adventures through history, encountering historical figures, places, and artifacts, we hope this site functions as a fun and educational guide. You can register to keep track of your contributions.

items.name: Forgotten Realms Wiki
items.title: Forgotten Realms Wiki
items.headline: Forgotten Realms Wiki
items.desc: The Forgotten Realms Wiki is an online wiki-based encyclopedia of the Forgotten Realms campaign setting for Dungeons & Dragons in all its editions. It aims to provide a complete and thorough reference work of the wealth of canon and licensed information, or "Realmslore", released in the decades since the setting's creation by Ed Greenwood. It covers the canonical sourcebooks and novels and other media, as well as officially licensed but non-canonical sources such as computer and video games and so on.

items.name: Battlestar Galactica Wiki
items.title: Battlestar Galactica Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Battlestar Galactica Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Battlestar Galactica Wiki, an encyclopedia based on the three main series, Battlestar Galactica (1978 Series), Battlestar Galactica (2004-2009 Series) and Battlestar Galactica: Blood & Chrome that anyone can edit. Battlestar Galactica is an American science fiction franchise created by Glen A. Larson. The franchise began with the original television series in 1978, and was later followed by a 1980 brief sequel series, a line of book adaptations, original novels, comic books, a board game, and video games. A re-imagined version of Battlestar Galactica aired as a two-part, three-hour miniseries developed by Ronald D. Moore and David Eick in 2003. The miniseries also led to a weekly television series, which later aired up until 2009. A prequel series, Caprica, aired in 2010. A two-hour pilot for a second spin-off series, Blood & Chrome, aired in 2012, with plans of continuing it into a regular series.

items.name: Buffyverse Wiki
items.title: Buffyverse Wiki
items.headline: Buffyverse Wiki
items.desc: Buffyverse Wiki is a community knowledge base devoted to Joss Whedon's Buffy the Vampire Slayer and its spin-off Angel. With over 5,000 pages, you'll find details on characters, episode guides, novels, and comics from both series.

items.name: The Lion King Wiki
items.title: The Lion King Wiki
items.headline: Step into the Circle of Life on The Lion King Wiki!
items.desc: The Lion King Wiki is a community database dedicated to one of Disney's most popular animated films, The Lion King. This film is a 1994 American animated feature film produced by Walt Disney Feature Animation and released by Walt Disney Pictures. It is the thirty-second animated feature in the Walt Disney Animated Classics as well as the highest-grossing traditionally animated film of all time in North America.

items.name: Hogan's Heroes
items.title: Hogan's Heroes
items.headline: Welcome to the Hogan's Heroes Wikia!
items.desc: The Hogan's Heroes Wikia is a collaborative project to create the most definitive, accurate, and accessible encyclopedia and reference database for everything related to Hogan's Heroes. Hogan's Heroes is a television sitcom that ran on the CBS television network from 1965 to 1971. Starring Bob Crane as Colonel Hogan, the show was set at Stalag 13, a German prisoner-of-war camp for Western Allied prisoners during World War II.

items.name: Half-Life Wiki
items.title: Half-Life Wiki
items.headline: Half-Life Wiki - "Prepare for unforseen consequences."
items.desc: Half-Life Wiki is a comprehensive encyclopedia focusing on the Half-Life and Portal universe by collecting information such as the games, characters, enemies, creatures, factions, locations, weapons, technology, and more.

items.name: Pikmin
items.title: Pikmin
items.headline: Welcome to the Pikmin Wiki!
items.desc: The Pikmin Wiki is a wikis about Nintendo's gaming franchise, Pikmin. The series features a playable captain controlling an army of diversely skilled and colored plant-animals called Pikmin, with their purpose being to help the captain survive, whether it be carry ship parts, treasures, or even massive fruit! The game features 3 games so far, as well as a heavy role in Nintendo's Super Smash Bros. Brawl, where Captain Olimar, the main character of the series, is a playable character. The series itself features many unique qualities, such as being one of the first console-only RTS games, unique technical structure (there is not a single texture in in-game files, only paint dogs that color the environments), and amazing environments. So come hop in and help us out!

items.name: The Chronicles of Narnia Wiki
items.title: The Chronicles of Narnia Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to WikiNarnia
items.desc:
Welcome to the Chronicles of Narnia Wiki, an encyclopedia for everything related to The Chronicles of Narnia, originally a series of seven books written by C.S. Lewis.

Our current goal is to expand this encyclopedia to include information on every Narnian subject possible. This encyclopedia, called a wiki, is special for the following reason: anyone can create or edit an article, so we can work together to form a database for Narnia fans.

Hundreds of people have created accounts on WikiNarnia over the years. Now have fun viewing, writing, or editing! You can be a WikiNarnian too!

items.name: MapleWiki
items.title: MapleWiki
items.headline: MapleWiki, the MapleStory database!
items.desc:
MapleStory is a free, two-dimensional, side-scrolling Massively Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game developed by Wizet and distributed by various companies. The game takes place in the "Maple World," which players must defend against monsters.

MapleWiki serves the latest English information from GlobalMS and the latest Korean information from KoreaMS as well as exclusive content from all versions.

items.name: Grand Theft Encyclopedia
items.title: Grand Theft Encyclopedia
items.headline: Grand Theft Encyclopedia
items.desc: ¡Bienvenido! La llamada Grand Theft Encyclopedia es la mayor base de datos sobre la saga Grand Theft Auto en español. El proyecto recopila la información sobre este título de Rockstar Games que revolucionó el género sandbox; incluyendo desde los primeros clásicos hasta el esperado Grand Theft Auto V.

items.name: LOST
items.title: LOST
items.headline: Welcome to the LOST wiki!
items.desc:
The LOST Wikia is a free LOST reference site which is being written collaboratively by the readers. We want to become the most up to date and the most reliable source for information about LOST. The LOST Wikia should be like a encyclopedia.

Lost is an Emmy Award and Golden Globe-winning American serial drama television series that follows the lives of plane crash survivors on a mysterious tropical island, after a passenger jet flying between Australia and the United States crashes somewhere in the South Pacific. Each episode typically features a primary storyline on the island as well as a secondary storyline from another point in a character's life. The show was created by Damon Lindelof, J.J. Abrams and Jeffrey Lieber, and is filmed primarily on location in Oahu, Hawaii. The pilot episode was first broadcast on September 22, 2004. Since then, five seasons have aired with the final sixth season startin 2010. The show is produced by ABC Studios, Bad Robot Productions and Grass Skirt Productions and airs on the ABC Network in the United States. Its incidental music is composed by Michael Giacchino. The current executive producers are Abrams, Lindelof, Carlton Cuse, Jack Bender, Jeff Pinkner and Bryan Burk. Because of its large ensemble cast and the cost of filming in Hawaii, the series is one of the most expensive on television.

items.name: Magic: The Gathering Wiki
items.title: Magic: The Gathering Wiki
items.headline: Magic: The Gathering Wiki
items.desc: Magic: The Gathering Wiki is dedicated to "The Gathering" (colloquially Magic or MTG), a collectible card game created by mathematics professor Richard Garfield and introduced in 1993 by Wizards of the Coast. Magic is the first example of the modern collectible card game genre and still thrives today, with an estimated six million players in over seventy countries.

items.name: RuneScape Wiki
items.title: RuneScape Wiki
items.headline: La Wikia de RuneScape en español
items.desc:
'''RuneScape Wiki''' fue creada el 10 de diciembre del 2005, por el jugador Lord Galarzaa.

Su propósito es brindar información sobre el juego de rol de multijugador en linea (MMORPG) RuneScape a personas que hablan español.

Cualquiera puede editar sus secciones.

<small>RuneScape® es una marca registrada de Jagex Sofware© 2000 - 2014 Jagex, Ltd.</small>

items.name: The BIONICLE Wiki
items.title: The BIONICLE Wiki
items.headline: BIONICLE Wiki
items.desc: BIONICLE Wiki is a hub of "Wiki Metru," a large community centering about wikis about Bionicle. The Bionicle Wiki is touted as being the most accurate wiki for information about the Bionicle Wiki. Any canon information from Bionicle sources is included in the wiki along with Brickipedia, BIONICLE Reviews Wiki, Custom BIONICLE Wiki, HeroPedia, Custom Hero Factory Wiki.

items.name: Futurama Wiki
items.title: Futurama Wiki
items.headline: Futurama Wiki
items.desc: Futurama Wiki en Español es la enciclopedia dedicada a la serie de televisión animada emitida por Fox. Este proyecto recopila toda la información relacionada con la serie creada por Matt Groening; que relata las aventuras de Fry en su viaje al futuro (año 3000), junto a sus amigos Bender, Leela y su descenciente Hubert.

items.name: Monster M*A*S*H
items.title: Monster M*A*S*H
items.headline: Welcome to the Monster M*A*S*H Wikia!
items.desc:
Welcome to Monster M*A*S*H, a wikia devoted to the novels by Richard Hooker and the movie and television series spun off from it!

You are welcome to browse what we have, create a new article (just click on one of the many red links you see), fix an existing article, or participate in one of our Community Projects to make the wiki a better information source.

items.name: AdventureQuest Wiki
items.title: AdventureQuest Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to AdventureQuest wiki
items.desc: AQWiki is a community dedicated to the Web-based Flash Role-Playing Game AdventureQuest, created and updated by Artix Entertainment, LLC. AQWiki aims to provide a comprehensive and accurate store of information about AdventureQuest that is mostly editable, with the exception of this main page to prevent vandalism. AdventureQuest requires nothing more than an Internet connection, a Web browser, and version 8.0 or above of the free plug-in Macromedia Flash to play.

items.name: Fire Emblem Wiki
items.title: Fire Emblem Wiki
items.headline: The Fire Emblem Wiki
items.desc: The Fire Emblem Wiki aims to be the definitive source of knowledge for the Fire Emblem franchise, containing information on the main series and spin-off games, as well as the characters, classes, locations, weapons, items, and races that make up the world of the games. If you want to help document information about the series or just share your love for it, know that your enthusiasm is welcome!

items.name: Mortal Kombat Wiki
items.title: Mortal Kombat Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Mortal Kombat Wiki!
items.desc: Mortal Kombat Wiki is a site dedicated to the Mortal Kombat series, featuring information about characters, locations, weapons, maps, screenshots, videos, walkthroughs, guides, fatalities, movies, and more. We'd love to have more users of the community to edit, chat and just talk about the series.

items.name: Looney Tunes Wiki
items.title: Looney Tunes Wiki
items.headline: Looney Tunes Wiki
items.desc: Eh, what's up, doc? Welcome to The Comprehensive Guide to Looney Tunes, a.k.a. Looney Tunes Wiki, a project based community with passionate editors and a source for all things "looney-tuney" since January 2006!

items.name: Charmed
items.title: Charmed
items.headline: Charmed Wiki
items.desc: Charmed Wiki is a collaborative project to help create a definitive encyclopedia for the hit television show Charmed. The wiki contains information on characters, episodes, cast, crew, powers, novels, comics, and more.

items.name: Brickipedia
items.title: Brickipedia
items.headline: Brickipedia, the LEGO wiki
items.desc: Brickipedia is a popular, well-known website, consisting of over 32k pages and counting, with users who strive to show off their knowledge for LEGO. Brickipedia, located at lego.wikia.com, is Wikia's largest LEGO Wiki, which was founded on March 4, 2005. Brickipedia's goal is to provide a free online Encyclopedia on everything LEGO. Twelve years after it was established, Brickipedia has reached a size of over 30,000 articles, and has a few hundred active users right now. Join the community and share your love of LEGO today.

items.name: The Harvest Moon Wiki

items.name: Ice Hockey Wiki
items.title: Ice Hockey Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Ice Hockey Wiki
items.desc:
Ice hockey is a team sport played on ice in which skaters use sticks to shoot a hard rubber hockey puck into their opponent's net to score points. In some countries, such as Canada and the United States, it is known as "hockey"; the name "ice hockey" is used in countries where "hockey" generally refers to field hockey.

A team usually consists of four lines of three forwards, three pairs of defensemen, and two goalies. Five members of each team skate up and down the ice trying to take the puck and score a goal against the opposing team. Each team has a goaltender who tries to stop the puck from going into the goal.

A fast-paced physical sport, hockey is most popular in areas of North America (particularly Canada and northern parts of the United States) and Europe. In North America, the National Hockey League (NHL) is the highest level for men ice hockey and the most popular. It is the official national winter sport of Canada, where the game enjoys immense popularity. The first organized game was played on March 3, 1875, in Montreal.

162 of 177 medals at the IIHF World Championships have been taken by seven nations: Canada, the Czech Republic, Finland, Russia, Slovakia, Sweden and the United States. Of the 66 medals awarded in men's competition at the Olympics from 1920, only six medals did not go to the one of those countries. All 12 Olympic and 36 IIHF World Women's Championships medals have gone to one of these seven countries, and every gold medal in both competitions has been won by either Canada or the United States.

Our goal is to collaborate with other fans in order to build a reliable, accurate resource with as much detailed information about episodes, characters, and story elements as possible. If you are a fan of either series - or both - or if you are simply interested in them, this is the place for you! All are welcome to join in and contribute here, so long as edits are constructive, discussions are positive, and both are relevant to these series. Hope to see you around!

items.name: Star Wars Games
items.title: Star Wars Games
items.headline: The force is strong at the Star Wars Game Wikia
items.desc: The Star Wars Games Wikia is a Wikia community dedicated to being the number one resource of everything related to Star War Games. These games include the popular Battlefront series, as well as the Knights of the Old Republic. Our community covers all the information related to the characters, the weapons, the stories, the levels, and whatever else is found within these games. Anybody is free to join and help make this Wikia a better resource.

items.name: Halo Fanon
items.title: Halo Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to Halo Fanon
items.desc: Halo Fanon is a community wiki dedicated to writing high quality fiction pertaining to the Halo universe Over ten years old and with over 10,000 pages produced by a population of ambitious fan fiction writers, Halo Fanon contributors are encouraged to write stories and articles about the Halo-verse, collaborate with other users and get feedback from more experienced users. Halo Fanon is a place to show off writing ability - or learn to write better with a constructive and dedicated community, and to interact with a community of Halo fans that care about the franchise.

items.name: Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki
items.title: Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki
items.headline: Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki
items.desc: Cardcaptor Sakura is an award-winning magical girl manga series first published in Japan. From the manga to the television series and more, we here at the Cardcaptor Sakura Wiki document everything there is to know about the series. As a Wikia site, anyone can edit, including you, so join us and share your knowledge and passion for Cardcaptor Sakura!

items.name: Arrested Development Wiki
items.title: Arrested Development Wiki
items.headline: There are dozens of us. Dozens!
items.desc:
Arrested Development is a ground-breaking sitcom that originally aired 53 episodes over three seasons from November 2, 2003 to February 10, 2006 on FOX. 

Since cancellation it has developed a cult following and its popularity has grown - a fourth season is in post-production and a film is tentatively planned.

It follows family man Michael Bluth as he tries to keep his family and business from collapsing after his father George is sent to prison for embezzling money. As the family adjusts from riches to rags Michael helps his mother Lucille keep up appearances, sister Lindsay and brother-in-law Tobias with their failed marriage, son George Michael and niece Maeby through adolescence, and brothers Buster and G.O.B. adjust to working life.

items.name: Wikitubia
items.title: Wikitubia
items.headline: The YouTube Wiki is waiting for you!
items.desc: Welcome to the YouTube Wiki! A Wiki for all things YouTube that anyone can edit.

items.name: Grand Theft Auto - GTA Wiki
items.title: Grand Theft Auto - GTA Wiki
items.headline: Grand Theft Auto Wiki
items.desc: Grand Theft Auto Wiki to ogromna baza danych o serii gier Grand Theft Auto wydawanych przez Rockstar Games od roku 1997. Wiki poświęcona jest wszystkiemu, co związane z serią – od dokładnych opisów gier i bohaterów po informacje dotyczące broni, pojazdów, miejsc czy misji dostępnych w grach.

items.name: Tekken Wiki
items.title: Tekken Wiki
items.headline: Bem-vindo à comunidade Tekken!
items.desc: Essa é uma enciclópedia que qualquer um pode editar, totalmente em português. A wiki Tekken é um guia para os jogadores e fãs da série Tekken de jogos de luta. A wiki contém informação sobre todos os jogos, quadrinhos & manga, lutadores, personagens, fases, movimentos, voices dos atores e as últimas notícias sobre os jogos em desenvolvimento! Há várias maneiras para novos membros participarem. Nós sempre estamos precisando de novas perspectivas, e também páginas que precisam de mais pesquisa. Então, mesmo que uma página não soe muito bem, não hesite em editá-la para que os novatos entendam melhor! Venha conferir!

items.name: PokéFanon
items.title: PokéFanon
items.headline: Create your own Pokemon, regions, trainers, teams and story lines!
items.desc: The PokéFanon Encyclopedia is a non-canon encylcopedia that is not endorsed by Gamefreak, Nintendo or any other for-profit company (as of yet!), and can be used by anyone! This wiki features fan-made Pokémon, regions, games and stories. Our goal is for you to create all the Pokemon you can imagine!!

items.name: Wakfu Wiki
items.title: Wakfu Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Wakfu Wiki
items.desc: Wakfu Wiki is a community collaboration about Wakfu, a turn-based tactical MMORPG under development by Ankama Studio. It takes place in the same fantasy world as Dofus, 1000 years later. Wakfu is a cross-media world. A number of projects, some completed, some in development, will all converge upon one single narrative, based in the world of Wakfu.

items.name: The Mighty Boosh Wiki
items.title: The Mighty Boosh Wiki
items.headline: Learn more about The Mighty Boosh
items.desc: Booshpedia, the Mighty Boosh wiki, is an unofficial fan created encyclopedia, whose purpose to provide information on absolutely every aspect of the Mighty Boosh phenomenon. This being a fan made site means that every vistor is not just allowed to edit, but encouraged to. Fans can also come and join a forum to meet other fans at The Might Boosh Forums or the Official Mighty Boosh forum.

items.name: The Formula 1 Wiki
items.title: The Formula 1 Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Formula 1 Wiki
items.desc:
The Formula 1 Wiki is Wikia's leading reference on the premier formula of motorsport, Formula One, in terms of size, detail and relevance.  With over 1000 pages and counting, we are growing at an exponential rate.  The Formula 1 Wiki has pages for all current Drivers and previous World Champions, as well as several pages for other notable drivers of the past.  In addition to drivers, many other key F1 personnel have their own pages, as do all current and several former F1 teams.  We are currently in the process of adding articles for all cars in F1 history, and completing pages regarding each season of F1 since 1950.

As an ongoing subject, each 2014 Season F1 race to date has a page, and each one is updated with stats and results on the Friday, Saturday and Sunday of each race weekend.

In the near future, we hope to cross the 1500 page boundary, and complete every article in order to make this wiki the ultimate F1 Reference!

items.name: QuakeWiki
items.title: QuakeWiki
items.headline: Welcome to Quake Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Quake Wiki, the best place to visit when you want read anything about id Software's timeless Quake series. Do you want to find more about the monsters of Quake or the maps of Quake 3 Arena? Or perhaps you want to add your own knowledge and experience to this unrivaled database of Quake. Everything is here for you, faithful fans of Quake, on this community site that anyone can edit, including you!

items.name: Smashpedia
items.title: Smashpedia
items.headline: Smashpedia - The Ultimate Smash Resource
items.desc:
Smashpedia was created to compile a complete repository of information relating to the Super Smash Bros. franchise, including the games themselves, characters, stages, strategies and techniques, competitive play, and more. You can join us and help edit this wiki with info from all the games.

You can also check out our pages on the new 3DS and Wii U games.

items.name: Kirby Wiki
items.title: Kirby Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Kirby Wiki!
items.desc:
This is the home of King Dedede, Meta Knight, Waddle Dee, and everything Kirby!


The wiki encompasses all aspects of the Kirby series - the characters, places, Kirby's signature copy abilities, soundtracks, and other goodies, in the anime series and all the games ever released over the series' 20-year history.


If you love all things Kirby, or wish to learn more, this is the place!

items.name: Fantendo - Nintendo Fanon Wiki
items.title: Fantendo - Nintendo Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Fantendo, the Nintendo Fanon Wiki
items.desc:
Fantendo is a community-based fanon Wiki. Though the wiki is based around Nintendo, we really accept fanon based around any type of video game! Come here to create and read about fan games, fan fiction, or even original fiction. In our community we discuss video gaming news and events as well.

Fantendo is a Wiki that was created in 2007. Our community has grown tremendously since then, with so many great additions to our userbase and our content. Our administration has grown as well; our administrators are supportive and humorous. 

Since 2007, we've grown to have almost 25,000 articles from enthusiastic Nintendo fans or other video game fans. It would be nice to have more great additions to our wiki from new users to the community! If you're going to join, don't be afraid to introduce yourself with a blogpost!

See and feel the excitement in the Fantendo Wiki!

items.name: High School Musical Wiki
items.title: High School Musical Wiki
items.headline: High School Musical Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to High School Musical Wikia! The High School Musical Wikia is dedicated to the High School Musical franchise that follows a group of students at East High School as they make their way through drama, first loves, competition, and singing! The High School Musical franchise is one of Disney's most successful movie series and is still popular to this day! Enter now to learn more!

items.name: Dragon Quest Wiki
items.title: Dragon Quest Wiki
items.headline: Dragon Quest Wiki
items.desc: Dragon Quest Wiki is devoted to Dragon Quest, a series of role-playing games made by Square Enix (originally Enix Co.) for a variety of video game platforms. It is the all-time best-selling video game series in Japan. Every Dragon Quest game is told primarily through the eyes a Hero named by the player, usually a prophesied "Chosen One" or a similar concept that requires him to rise against a new evil.

items.name: Rainbow Six Wiki
items.title: Rainbow Six Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Rainbow Six Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Rainbow Six Wiki! Our wiki is dedicated to Tom Clancy's video game, Rainbow Six. Read through our comprehensive database featuring information about the different Rainbox Six games, characters, weapons and more on this wiki. We encourage new users to join the wiki to read, contribute, and edit!

items.name: Worms Wiki
items.title: Worms Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Worms Wiki!
items.desc: The largest Worms database.

items.name: God of War Wiki
items.title: God of War Wiki
items.headline: God of War Wiki
items.desc: God of War Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia for everything related to the God of War series. Here you will find detailed information on every game as well as the gods, titans, enemies, items, and more.

items.name: WikiHero
items.title: WikiHero
items.headline: Welcome to WikiHero, the Guitar Hero Wiki
items.desc: Guitar Hero is a rhythm video game series originally created by Harmonix in 2005, and later developed by Neversoft.   In Guitar Hero, players use the strum bar along with the fret buttons to play notes that scroll down the screen along a fretboard.   Points are gained for each correct note played.  The Wiki covers all aspects of the series and its spin-offs, and all are welcome to contribute!

items.name: Soulcalibur Wiki
items.title: Soulcalibur Wiki
items.headline: Soulcalibur Wiki
items.desc: Soulcalibur Wiki is a site based on the Soul series of fighting games developed by Namco. It has information on all of the aspects of each game, such as characters, various weapons, stages, secrets, and more.

items.name: Metal Gear Wiki
items.title: Metal Gear Wiki
items.headline: Metal Gear Wiki, la enciclopedia de la saga Metal Gear
items.desc: Metal Gear Wiki es la enciclopedia en español dedicada a la franquicia de videojuegos Metal Gear. Se trata de un proyecto que trata de recopilar toda la información relacionada con este producto creado por Konami; englobando desde los primeros clásicos, la exitosa Metal Gear Solid, otras sagas secundarias como Rising y Ac!d, y el más esperado Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain.

items.name: Rocky Wiki
items.title: Rocky Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Rocky wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Rocky Wiki site!!! This website is a tribute to the popular film series Rocky, which has grossed more than $1 billion at the worldwide box office. The first film in the series, Rocky was the highest grossing film of 1976, and won three Oscars, including Best Picture. The film received many positive reviews and turned it's lead actor, Sylvester Stallone, into a major star. To date, it has spawned five similarly high-grossing sequels: Rocky II, III, IV, V, Rocky Balboa and a spinoff film Creed.  You are welcome to browse what we have, create a new article (just click on one of the red links you see), fix an existing article, or participate in one of our Community Projects to make the wiki a better information source.

items.name: SporeWiki
items.title: SporeWiki
items.headline: Welcome to SporeWiki
items.desc:
SporeWiki is a knowledge database dedicated to Spore, the computer simulation video game developed by Will Wright.  Affiliated with Sims Wiki, also developed by Wright, Spore is innovative in technology of the game design, as well as the expansive range of sci-fi game play.

SporeWiki has an active community who maintain unique projects such as the Taxonomy project and the SporeWiki Fiction Universe and any registered user is free to join.

items.name: Ben 10 Wiki
items.title: Ben 10 Wiki
items.headline: Ben 10 Planet
items.desc: Ben 10 Planet is the ultimate resource for the Ben 10 franchise, consisting of 10,000 pictures and over 1,600 pages of detailed information on the TV series as well as the animated and live-action movies.

items.name: Far Cry Wiki
items.title: Far Cry Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Far Cry Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Far Cry Wiki. The Far Cry Series encyclopaedia with in-depth information on these first person shooters. Find everything about Far Cry, from the first game to Far Cry Primal. This wiki covers the games, the DLC's and every small detail in this first person shooter series.

items.name: Naruto Fanon Wiki
items.title: Naruto Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Naruto Fanon Wiki
items.desc: Naruto Fanon Wiki is undoubtedly dedicated to fanon/fanfiction about Naruto, the popular manga and anime series. In their own words, Naruto Fanon Wiki strives to become the preeminent and largest Naruto Fanon fanbase in the world and has over 25000 pages worth of content that readers of the series would enjoy.

items.name: The Sopranos Wiki
items.title: The Sopranos Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Sopranos Wiki!
items.desc: The Sopranos is an American television drama created by David Chase. The series revolves around the New Jersey-based Italian-American mobster Tony Soprano (James Gandolfini) and the difficulties he faces as he tries to balance the conflicting requirements of his home life and the criminal organization he heads. Those difficulties are often highlighted through his ongoing professional relationship with psychiatrist Jennifer Melfi (Lorraine Bracco). The show features Tony's family members and Mafia associates in prominent roles and story arcs, most notably his wife Carmela (Edie Falco) and his cousin and protégé Christopher Moltisanti (Michael Imperioli).

items.name: Shadowrun Wiki
items.title: Shadowrun Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Shadowrun Wiki!
items.desc: Shadowrun is a role-playing game set in a fictional alternate universe. Shadowrun combines cyberpunk and high fantasy to create a near future world where technology has advanced beyond our understanding, powerful mega corporations control everyday life, and magic and classical fantasy races have returned to the world.

items.name: Monster Hunter Wiki
items.title: Monster Hunter Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Monster Hunter Wiki
items.desc: Hunters unite! Monster Hunter Wiki is the ultimate guide for the Monster Hunter series, the first being released in Japan in March of 2004 and was later released in North America in September of 2004. Monster Hunter is a hack and slash, strategy adventure game. The latest version, Monster Hunter 4, was release in 2013. This wiki contains community contributed information documenting all of the games (English and Japanese), monsters, quests, weapons, items, areas, Entertainment and much more. Anyone can contribute and we encourage you to do so. Come join our community!

items.name: Grand Theft Wiki
items.title: Grand Theft Wiki
items.headline: Bienvenue sur Grand Theft Wiki !
items.desc: Notre wiki est entièrement consacré aux nombreux épisodes de la célèbre série Grand Theft Auto créée par l’éditeur de jeux vidéo américain Rockstar Games. Le tout nouveau Grand Theft Auto V est à présent disponible sur la plupart des plateformes et nous sommes toujours en quête d’informations sur ce dernier-né, alors n’hésitez pas à jeter un coup d’œil à notre wiki et à nous donner un coup de main si le cœur vous en dit !

items.name: Czarodziejka z Księżyca Wiki
items.title: Czarodziejka z Księżyca Wiki
items.headline: Czarodziejka z Księżyca Wiki
items.desc: Jest to polska baza danych o serii Czarodziejka z Księżyca. Serię zapoczątkowała manga stworzona przez Naoko Takeuchi, na podstawie której powstała popularna seria anime, mająca 200 odcinków, a także trzy filmy fabularne, produkcje muzyczne i teatralne, gry wideo oraz serial live-action. Jako legenda gatunku magical girls jest pozycją obowiązkową dla osób uważających się za znawców gatunku. Seria przyczyniła się do rozwoju i ewolucji gatunku mahō-shōjo wprowadzając nowe idee.

items.name: Harry Potter Fanon Wiki
items.title: Harry Potter Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Harry Potter Fanon Wiki!
items.desc: You have reached an encyclopedic resource and community gathering spot for all things related to the vast and diverse world of Harry Potter fan-fiction and fanon. As of now, we are the #1 Harry Potter fanon database anyone can edit.

items.name: Transformers Fanon Wiki
items.title: Transformers Fanon Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Transformers Fanon Wikia!
items.desc:
The Transformers Fanon Wikia, commonly called Transfanon, is a wikia for making up transformers characters, story lines, or anything else Transformers related. Everything here is non-canon! None of it is real! 

We allow users to make their own stories without them being deleted like they would be on the Transformers Wiki. They would only be deleted if they have offensive text or have no purpose and have little sense (Joke Articles are an exception).

Happy editing!

items.name: Phantasy Star Wiki
items.title: Phantasy Star Wiki
items.headline: All things Phantasy Star, from the original Sega series to the current PSO2
items.desc: The Phantasy Star Wiki is a wiki created to cover everything related to Phantasy Star games - the wiki covers the original series, the Phantasy Star Online series, and the Phantasy Star Universe series. With information about all the different characters, weapons and armour, and areas in the Phantasy Star games, including maps and walkthroughs.

items.name: Chuck Wiki
items.title: Chuck Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Chuck Wiki!
items.desc: The Chuck Wiki is a fan created Intersect like database which is dedicated to providing detailed information on all aspects of the NBC Television Series, Chuck. This wiki format is designed to allow any Chuck fan to contribute to its pages. We encourage new users to join the wiki to read and edit the pages!

items.name: StarCraftWiki
items.title: StarCraftWiki
items.headline: Bienvenidos a StarCraft Wiki
items.desc: La franquicia StarCraft está basada en una saga de videojuegos de estrategia en tiempo real, desarrollada por la compañía Blizzard Entertainment. Es similar a otra exitosa franquicia anterior de la compañía, Warcraft. Su primera entrega, StarCraft, fue el juego más vendido de 1998, con un total de 9,5 millones de copias desde su lanzamiento; convirtiéndose asimismo en el tercer juego más vendido en la historia del equipo.

items.name: That's So Raven wiki
items.title: That's So Raven wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the That's So Raven Wikia!
items.desc:
This wikia is dedicated to chronicling the tv show, That's So Raven, which is an American sitcom television series. It debuted on the Disney Channel on January 17, 2003, and ended its run on November 10, 2007. 

The show is set in San Francisco and revolves around teenager Raven Baxter, played by Raven Symoné, her friends Eddie aka Orlando Brown and Chelsea aka Anneliese van der Pol, and her family members focusing on brother Cory Baxter aka Kyle Massey. The title character draws on her talent as a fashion designer, ingenuity, psychic powers and a variety of disguises to get into and out of amusing adolescent and pre-adolescent situations..

items.name: Die Hard Wiki
items.title: Die Hard Wiki
items.headline: Yippie Ki Yay! An explosive guide to the hit movies.
items.desc: The Die Hard wiki is dedicated to documenting the heroics of John McClane, the man that is always in the wrong place at the wrong time. The wiki includes information on the four Die Hard films, John McClane, his various enemies, allies, and the areas that populate the Die Hard universe. This is a growing wiki and any help in detailing articles will not go unappreciated.

items.name: Doctor Who Fanon
items.title: Doctor Who Fanon
items.headline: Welcome to the Doctor Who Fanon Wikia!
items.desc: Doctor Who Fanon is Wikia's first & largest Doctor Who Fan Fiction site. Our goal is to provide a free online outlet that gives you the means to write your own adventures about the Doctor Who Universe. Since its establishment in 2007, Doctor Who Fanon has reached the size of over 2,000 articles. May your fictions be about The Doctor, those ruthless Daleks, or the nasty Cybermen, you can let your imagination take flight on our site!

items.name: Witcher Wiki
items.title: Witcher Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Witcher Wiki
items.desc: Witcher Wiki is a community site that aims to create the best resource for everything to do with The Witcher, including the books, games, TV show, movie, and more. Anyone can come and read what we have and contribute knowledge of their own. If you need help editing, please ask an Admin and we will be happy to help!

items.name: S.T.A.L.K.E.R. Wiki
items.title: S.T.A.L.K.E.R. Wiki
items.headline: Learn how to survive the horrors of the Zone with the S.T.A.L.K.E.R. wikia
items.desc:
The S.T.A.L.K.E.R. Wiki is an English wikia documenting the S.T.A.L.K.E.R. franchise made by GSC game world.

The S.T.A.L.K.E.R. series itself, is an open-sandbox FPS game that combines RPG elements and a large selection of wide-open maps with plenty to raid and explore.  This is made more immersive by the game's "A-life", an innovative life-simulation system meant to simulate a living environment, even without the player's intervention.

Here, You play as a "stalker", one of the many illegal residents of the Chernobyl Exclusion Zone, the site of the 1986 disaster in Ukraine where the entirety of Chernobyl was declared inhospitable due to the Lenin Memorial Reactor #4 suffering a critical meltdown and contaminating the area around it with lethal amounts of radiation.

However, after a secret Soviet experiment within the Zone gone awry, it warped reality within the Zone, creating physics-bending anomalies and deadly mutants that were once considered unthinkable.It has also, however, spawned a number of highly valuable "artifacts" and other specimens of scientific interest that triggered a proverbial gold-rush that led to the Zone being largely populated by these fortune-seeking "stalkers".

Now, you must survive these reality-defying horrors and monsters, all the while battling the Zone's harsh elements and your fellow men, a large number of whom won't mind gunning you down for the scarce supplies you carry, all the while finding more and more about the Zone and its secrets as you head deeper into the center.

Its chaos and anarchy in this merciless, man-made hell. How you will survive is up to you.

The wiki currently contains over a thousand articles containing information on every personae, shooter, armored suit, mutant, quest, anomaly, artifact, lore, location, and virtually everything you need to survive the irradiated and twisted wasteland of the Zone.

So come in and visit! Don't just stand there, stalker!

items.name: BioShock Wiki
items.title: BioShock Wiki
items.headline: BioShock Wiki
items.desc: BioShock Wiki is a database for the BioShock video game series. The wiki is dedicated to preserving all information related to the worlds of Rapture and Columbia, including characters, enemies, weapons, items, walkthroughs and more.

items.name: Danny Phantom Wiki
items.title: Danny Phantom Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Danny Phantom Wiki!
items.desc:
The wiki about Danny Phantom that anyone can edit. Please feel free to help us create one of the largest sites on Butch Hartman's popular show Danny Phantom. 

Danny Phantom is an American animated television show created by Butch Hartman for Nickelodeon, produced by Billionfold Studios. It was originally run on April 3, 2004 up to August 24, 2007. The show is about Danny Fenton, a teenage half-ghost boy, who frequently saves his town and the world from ghost attacks, while attempting to keep his ghost half a secret. It is distributed outside the United States by the Canadian animation company, Nelvana, the same as The Fairly OddParents (also created by Hartman).

items.name: Aion Wiki
items.title: Aion Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Aion Wiki!
items.desc: Aion Wiki is dedicated to becoming the best community resource for Aion, a massively multiplayer online role-playing game (MMORPG) released by NCsoft, a major Korean game developer. Aion Wiki covers gameplay information, characters, news, classes, races, and more. Come immerse yourself in the world of Atreia.

items.name: Wakfu
items.title: Wakfu
items.headline: Wakfu Wiki
items.desc: Willkommen im Wakfu-Wiki! Wakfu ist ein Massively Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game des französischen Entwicklers Ankama. Es stellt den Nachfolger zu Dofus dar und spielt 1000 Jahre nach dessen Geschichte. Teilt euer Wissen bei uns mit den anderen Usern und lest nach, was euch interessiert.

items.name: Tekken Wiki
items.title: Tekken Wiki
items.headline: Join the Tekken Wiki
items.desc: Tekken Wiki is the ultimate guide for players and fans of the Tekken series of fighting games. The wiki contains information on all the games, comics & manga, fighters, characters, stages, moves, voice actors, and the latest on the newest developing games! There are plenty ways for new members to get involved. We are constantly in need of new expertise and perspective, not to mention pages that need further research. So even if a page doesn't sound quite right, don't hestitate to edit it in a way that newcomers may understand a bit better! So come check us out!

items.name: Metallica Wiki
items.title: Metallica Wiki
items.headline: Learn more about Metallica!
items.desc: If you are a Heavy Metal fan or Thrash Metal fan, you've heard of the band Metallica at one point in you're life. Always wanted to learn about them? No Problem! We here at the Metallica wiki have more about the band than their official website does! This is the number one place to go if you want to learn about the kings of Thrash Metal themselves.

items.name: Killzone Wiki
items.title: Killzone Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Killzone Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Killzone Wiki, the community site for the Killzone Wiki that anyone can edit, including you. We are creating the biggest guide to the Killzone Game, and you can help. If you want to share your knowledge and passion for the Killzone game, join us today and help out your fellow fans on the wiki!

items.name: Winniepedia
items.title: Winniepedia
items.headline: Visit the Hundred Acre Wood at Winniepedia
items.desc: Winniepedia is the Wikia wiki for everything about that cubby, tubby, silly old bear Winnie the Pooh and his friends in the Hundred Acre Wood. Whether you're a fan of the original A.A. Milne books or the Disney incarnations, we have it here - from "Return to Pooh Corner" to "My Friends Tigger & Pooh, to the Hundred Acre Wood as seen in the game "Kingdom Hearts." Visit with Pooh, Tigger, Rabbit, Kanga, Roo and more!

items.name: Death Note Wiki
items.title: Death Note Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Death Note Wiki!
items.desc: Death Note Wiki is a community database about the Death Note series created by Tsugumi Ohba and Takeshi Obata. Death Note centers around a high school student named Light Yagami, who discovers a supernatural notebook that allows him to kill anyone simply by writing the victim's name while picturing his or her face. Disgusted with the amount of crime in the world, Light decides to use the notebook to eliminate criminals and become the "god" of a "New World," inhabited only by those that he deems "good." Now accompanying Light is a Shinigami (Death God) named Ryuk, who dropped the notebook to Earth from the Shinigami Realm. After a number of criminals suddenly die, talk on the internet leads to the deaths being attributed to a mysterious killer that is deemed "Kira" (the Japanese pronunciation of the English word "killer"). As the death toll quickly continues to rise, law enforcement agencies around the world begin to take notice and all are unable to find any reason for the deaths to have had occurred. Unbeknownst to Light, a Detective known only as "L" has also noticed the strange deaths and is already on Lights tail. After publicly voicing his intention to find Kira and bring him to justice, a cat and mouse game begins between Light and L as they both try to stay ahead of the other and uncover their opponents name.

items.name: エバークエスト2 Wiki
items.title: エバークエスト2 Wiki
items.headline: エバークエスト2(日本語版)へようこそ!
items.desc:
エバークエスト2(以下略：EQ2)(日本語版)は、ソニーオンラインエンターテイメントの運営するオンラインロールプレイングゲームについてのコミュニティーです。EQ2はプレイヤーが剣と魔法の世界を舞台に20の種族と26の職業から自分の分身を作り、他のプレイヤー達と共に冒険を繰り広げるゲームです。このコミュニティーでは常にゲームに関する最新情報をアップデードしています。また、お薦めのクエスト、追加された機能の紹介や初心者の方へのガイドなども紹介させて頂いています。
誰でも編集できるコミュニティーですのでゲームに関することであれば是非書き込んで下さい。初めての方はアカウントを取得することをお薦めします。

items.desc:

Any contribution or help is immensely appreciated. Please do try to ensure that any contributions are accurate - we want all our users to have the best time possible and not be disappointed by unclear or incorrect information.

items.name: Jak and Daxter Wiki
items.title: Jak and Daxter Wiki
items.headline: The Jak and Daxter Wiki
items.desc: Jak and Daxter Wiki is dedicated to the successful video game franchise "Jak and Daxter," originally developed by Naughty Dog for the PlayStation 2, then by Ready At Dawn for the PSP and most recently High Impact Games for the PS2 and PSP. Currently, six games in the series have been released, with Jak as the primary playable character in all except Daxter for the PSP. The latest game, The Lost Frontier released November 3, 2009.

items.headline: Beyblade Wiki
items.desc: Beyblade Wiki is a collaborative database about the various seasons of the Beyblade anime series, as well as every Beyblade toy. The goal of Beyblade Wiki is to become the largest online database for all things Beyblade.

Welcome to the Metalocalypse Wiki!

This wiki is dedicated to chronicling information about Metalocalypse, which is an American animated television series on Adult Swim created by Brendon Small and Tommy Blacha. Read about the four seasons of the show, the different characters, the music featured on the show, and more! We welcome new users to contribute to and edit the wiki.

items.title: Madness Combat Wiki

items.desc: Madness Combat is a series of flash animation made by Krinkels. The main theme of this is mass killing and guys with crosses for faces. Currently there are 9 episodes and a flashback episode currently called 'Madness Combat 5.5' is currently in the works. So if you're a fan of Madness Combat then you have come to the right place!

items.name: Burn Wiki
items.title: Burn Wiki
items.headline: BURN Notice Wiki
items.desc:
Burn Notice is a TV Series all about spies! It focuses on a spy, Michael Westen and his life after he receives his burn notice. 

What's a Burn Notice you ask?

It's an official document issued from one agency to other agencies stating that a source or asset is no longer reliable. This results in all of the individual's information to be disregarded or "BURNED".

Each episode focuses partly on Michael trying to figure why he received his 'burn notice' as well as dealing with clients who need his help. The awesome narration in each episode by Michael could give you tips in being a spy.

Burn Notice is a quality show with the edge and attitude to BURN.

Come check out our wiki and learn more about spies (like Michael) and spy knowledge/wisdom.

items.name: Eureka Wiki
items.title: Eureka Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Eureka Wiki!
items.desc: Eureka is an American science fiction television series that premiered on the Syfy channel. The show is set in a fictional town in the Pacific Northwest called Eureka, Oregon. Populated mostly by scientific geniuses working for Global Dynamics, an advanced research facility responsible for many technological breakthroughs. Each episode features a mysterious, accidental, or intentional misuse of technology, which the town sheriff, Jack Carter, then solves with the help of town scientists.

items.name: Capcom Database
items.title: Capcom Database
items.headline: Capcom Wiki
items.desc: The Capcom Database is devoted to Capcom, the developers and creators of popular long-running games such as Resident Evil and Street Fighter. Over the years, Capcom has created some of the biggest and longest running franchises in video gaming history since starting out in 1979. Capcom Database has over over 1000 pages on Capcom games, characters, covers, fan art and much more.
